ðŸ¤” Q. Write a program to print odd number between 1 to 10.

# Code

No = 0                    
while (No <= 10):  

  if (No%2 != 0):            
    print(No)

  No += 1


- O/P.:
1
3
5
7
9




ðŸ¤” Q. Write a program to check is number entered by the user is odd or even.

# Code

a = int(input("Enter No. = "))

if (a%2 == 0):
  print("Even Number")

else:
  print("Odd Number")


- O/P.:  
Enter No. = 7
Odd Number




ðŸ¤” Q. Write a program to identify the number is even or odd using function.

# Code

def Even_Odd(no):

  if (no%2 == 0):
    print("Even Number")
  else:
    print("Odd Number")

No = int(input("Enter Number = "))
Even_Odd(No)


- O/P.:
Enter Number = 7
Odd Number
